# Agents Layer (`packages/agents`)

Per `docs/05-agent-architecture.md`:

- Stateful flows use LangGraph with versioned Pydantic state schemas
- Tools invoke application services through explicit interfaces
- All LLM outputs schema-validated before persistence
- Record: model, provider, prompt version, schema version, token usage, latency, run ID
- Agents MUST NOT write to Neo4j or canonical tables directly
- Agents MUST NOT access sources outside caller authorization
- Agents MUST NOT invent missing sources

## Human-in-the-loop gates

Mandatory review: ontology changes, destructive merges, low-confidence claims, access-policy changes.

## Prompts

Versioned prompt templates live in `packages/prompts/`. Reference prompt version in audit records.
